'''Nastisizim''' (frah Griik γνωστικός ''gnostikos'', "ab nalij", frah γνῶσις ''gnōsis'', nalij) a madan toerm we kiatigaraiz kalekshan a ienshent rilijans uufa adierent shon di [[Niecha|matiirial wol]]&nbsp;– we deh vyuu az kriet bai di demyoerj&nbsp;– ah imbries di pirichual wol.<ref>Fi di kamplexiti a nastisizim, si Larry W. Hurtado, ''Lord Jesus Christ: Devotion to Jesus in Earliest Christianity'', 2005. Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing, pp. 519–561</ref> Nastik aidie influens nof ienshent rilijans<ref>John Hinnel, ''The Penguin Dictionary of Religion'', 1997, Penguin Books UK </ref> we tiich se ''[[nasis]]'' (vieriosli intoerprit az nalij, [[Inlaitnment (pirichual)|inlaitnment]], [[salvieshan]], [[Imansipieshan]] ar 'wannis wid Gad') kiah riich bai praktis filanchropi tu di paint a poersnal [[Vou a pavati|pavati]], [[Vou a selibesi|sexyual abstinens]] (az for az pasibl fi [[wikt:en:disciple|eni we ier]], intayali fi [[Inishieshan|inishiet]]) ah dilijentli saach fi [[wizdam]] bai elp ada wandem.<ref name=gph>Tobias Churton, ''Gnostic Philosophy: From Ancient Persia to Modern Times'', Inner Traditions, VA USA, [https://www.google.fi/books?id=mvpkAwAAQBAJ&lpg=PT12&ots=QNHwTiVkhf&dq=%22From%20Ancient%20Persia%20to%20Modern%20Times%22&lr&pg=PP1#v=onepage&q&f=false|year=2005|ISBN=978-159477-035-7]</ref> Ousomeba, praktis vieri mongx demde uu eh Nastik.

